The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slipped 0.2
percent to 1,678.13 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, paring an
earlier loss of as much as 0.8 percent. The dollar-denominated
RTS Index fell 0.4 percent to 1,927.82.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO AvtoVAZ (AVAZ RX) gained for a second day, rising 2.7
percent to 27.03 rubles after the Russian carmaker returned to
profit last year as the government encouraged new car sales with
a rebate program.  OAO Mostotrest (MSTT RX) gained for the first day in three
after a unit of the Russian construction company won a contract
worth 7.45 billion rubles ($267 million) to upgrade Moscowâ€™s
Vnukovo airport. Its shares rose 1.2 percent to 220.6 rubles.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a Russian silver producer, gained
by its most in more than three weeks, adding 2.4 percent to
495.7 rubles as futures for the metal advanced.  To contact the reporter on this story:
